Nguyen Quang Trung is a Junior Software Engineer, AI Engineer with academic experience focused on cutting-edge machine learning and big data solutions. Their core expertise encompasses advanced Computer Vision techniques, specifically real-time object detection using YOLOv11, alongside foundational AI algorithms like Alpha-Beta Pruning, Uniform Cost Search (UCS), and A* for intelligent decision-making and optimized search methods. They possess strong capabilities in Big Data processing, implementing algorithms such as Apriori with Hadoop MapReduce for frequent itemset discovery and PageRank with PySpark for web graph analysis, leveraging distributed storage and resource management principles. Academic projects include training a custom YOLOv11 model on 5K+ annotated frames for football object detection, achieving high mAP and low-latency real-time deployment with CUDA, developing AI for Tic-Tac-Toe and Pacman using Alpha-Beta Pruning and A* with proposed heuristics, and optimizing Apriori and PageRank algorithms for scalability across large datasets.
Technically, Nguyen Quang Trung is proficient in Python, Java, C#, and C/C++, with hands-on experience in machine learning frameworks like PyTorch and TensorFlow, and computer vision libraries such as OpenCV. They are skilled in big data ecosystems including Hadoop (HDFS, YARN, MapReduce) and Apache Spark (PySpark, Spark DataFrame APIs, Spark SQL). Database management experience includes MySQL, MS SQL Server, and MongoDB. Development tools and platforms include Git and Jupyter. Their foundational knowledge spans Data Structures (Graph Data Structure, Adjacency List, Traversal Algorithms), Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), Heuristics (Admissibility, Consistency), Data Partitioning, Preprocessing, Data Augmentation, and Web Graph Analysis, complemented by strong problem-solving, teamwork, critical thinking, and self-learning abilities.